course: main course
servings: 2
time required: 40 minutes
---

Halve the @butternut squash{1} lengthways (no need to peel!) and scoop out the seeds. Chop
into 2cm pieces. Trim the tops from the @green beans{150%g}, then chop into thirds.
Roughly chop the @coriander{1%bunch}(stalks and all). Drain and rinse the
@chickpeas{1%400g can} in a #sieve{}.

Heat a splash of @oil{a splash} in a large #saucepan{} over medium-high heat. Add the
butternut, stir and cook until it begins to soften, ~{5%minutes}. Add the
@jalfrezi spice mix{1} blend, half the coriander and the @tomato puree{30%g}. Stir and
cook until fragrant, ~{1%minute}. Add the chickpeas and the @water for the curry{250%ml}.

Bring to the boil, then stir in half the @vegetable stock powder{1}, stir to dissolve
the stock pot, then lower the heat to medium. Put the lid on and leave the curry to
bubble away until the butternut and lentils are soft, ~{20-25%minutes}. Stir every now
and then to make sure the lentils aren't catching on the bottom of the pan.

Meanwhile, pour the @water for the rice{300%ml} into another large saucepan along with
the @ground turmeric{2} and remaining stock pot. Bring to the boil and stir to dissolve
the stock pot, then pour in the @basmati rice{150%g}, lower the heat to medium and pop
a lid on the saucepan. Cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the pan from the heat and
set aside (still covered) for another ~{10%minutes}.

> TIP: The rice will finish in its own steam.

When the curry has been cooking for ~{15%minutes}, add the green beans, stir and pop
the lid back on. Cook until the beans are tender, ~{7-10%minutes}. When the beans are
cooked, remove the curry from the heat. Add a splash of water if the curry is a bit
thick. Season to taste with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste} if needed.

Fluff up the rice with a #fork{} and stir through the remaining coriander. Share the
rice between your #bowls{} and top with the butternut curry. For a dairy free option
enjoy now. For a creamier curry, finish with a generous dollop of
@greek style natural yoghurt{150%g}. Enjoy!